---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const publishDate = '2026-03-18';
const modifiedDate = '2026-03-18';
const author = 'David Hagon';
const readTime = '7 min read';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What should I look for in a computer repair shop?',
    answer:
      'Look for transparent pricing, genuine Google reviews from local customers, a no fix no fee policy, clear communication about what\'s wrong and what it will cost, and an established track record. A good repair shop should be happy to explain the problem in plain English and give you a quote before starting work.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Are chain stores or independent repair shops better?',
    answer:
      'Independent shops are typically cheaper, faster, and more personal. You deal with the actual technician rather than a front-desk person relaying messages. Chain stores have higher overheads which get passed on to you, and your computer may be sent off-site for repair, adding days to the turnaround.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I know if a computer repair shop is trustworthy?',
    answer:
      'Check their Google reviews for consistent positive feedback from real local customers. Look for a physical presence or established business history. A trustworthy shop will give you a clear diagnosis and quote before starting work, offer a no fix no fee guarantee, and never pressure you into unnecessary upgrades or repairs.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Should I use a local repair shop or an online service?',
    answer:
      'For most repairs, local is better. You get face-to-face communication, faster turnaround (often same day), no shipping risks, and you know exactly who is handling your computer and your data. Online services can work for specific issues like data recovery from specialist labs, but for general repairs a local shop is the way to go.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What questions should I ask before handing over my computer?',
    answer:
      'Ask: What do you think the problem is? How much will the diagnostic cost? Will you give me a quote before doing any paid work? What\'s your no fix no fee policy? How long will it take? Do you guarantee your work? These questions will quickly tell you whether you\'re dealing with a professional or not.',
  },
];
